            "is_constituent_info": false,
            "is_prior_year_field": false,
            "draft_value": "* $1.75 billion increase over the FY 2026 enacted level of $7.25 billion to restore agency stability and mission momentum\n* Funding restores critical capability following budget volatility that led to thousands of contractor layoffs and civil servant departures\n* Investment level required to meet scientific milestones and project timelines established by the National Academies' peer-review process",
            "rationale": "Justifies the $9B ask by referencing the $1.75B increase over FY26 enacted levels and citing the workforce stability talking points.",
